hoodMarket: Wilmington’s industrial market draws its strength from the Port of Wilmington, a full-service, deepwater port that ranks number one in North America for imports of fresh fruits and juice concentrates, with the largest dock-side cold storage facility on the continent. ,Serviced by I-95, U.S. Route 202, and the Delaware Memorial Bridge (which feeds directly into the New Jersey Turnpike), goods can be transported from here to Philadelphia, New York City and Washington D.C., in under two hours.,Distributors and business services firms including Intercontinental Services of Delaware, Superior Distribution, and Iron Mountain maintain large industrial facilities here. Specialty chemical manufacturers including Prince Minerals and Delchem also account for a large share of industrial activity, along with building materials supply firms including Midsouth Building Supply, R.C. Fabricators, and Steel Suppliers Erectors.,Gulftainer, a UAE-based port operator which took ownership of the Port of Wilmington in 2018, plans to more than quadruple the port’s container volume by 2023 via a $600 million investment that expands its existing port terminals. This could be a boon for economic activity in the region and allow the port to diversify well beyond refrigerated cargo, which currently represents about 80% of its business.

Zoned general industrial, the building includes natural gas for heat, air conditioning in the warehouse, water supplied by United Water and sewer by New Castle County. The site offers convenient access to the Delaware Memorial Bridge, Port of Wilmington, and the entire northeast corridor. Site offers incredible access to Route 141, I-95, I-295, I-495, while four states are accessible within 30 minutes. The area offers a friendly business environment in the Town of Newport.

propOverview:
SVN is pleased to offer up to +/- 12,160 square feet of office/industrial space for lease at 1620 Dean Forest Road situated on +/- 1.34 acres of land with P-I-2 (Heavy Industrial) Zoning. The interior configuration is comprised of (2) Suites, which can be leased together or separately.
Suite (1) is +/-7,360 SF and includes +/- 1,200 SF of office space in addition to +/- 6,160 SF of warehouse space. The office portion includes an open reception area, two private offices, a break area and a restroom. The warehouse portion includes single and three phase power, 14’ ceiling height, (4) 12’ x 12’ roll up doors and a shared mobile loading dock ramp.
Suite (2) is +/-4,800 SF and includes +/- 1,200 SF of office space in addition to +/- 3,600 SF of warehouse space. The office portion includes an open reception area, three private offices and a restroom. The warehouse portion includes single and three phase power, 14’ ceiling height, (2) 12’ x 12’ roll up doors and a shared mobile loading dock ramp.
This central location, which is just north of Interstate 16 and south of Highway 80 provides quick access to many areas of Savannah including Pooler and Downtown along with major area thoroughfares including Interstate 16, Interstate 95, Highway 80 and Chatham Parkway. Traffic counts exceed 16,000 vehicles per day along Dean Forest and nearly 59,000 vehicles per day along Interstate 16. Several major employers, such as Savannah/Hilton Head International Airport, JCB and Gulfstream are located nearby.

Ingress/egress to the property is achieved via 3 separate streets, which provides drive-through capabilities. Located in mid-Pinellas County, Interstate 275 is a short 6 minute drive and is accessible by either Gandy Boulevard (Exit 28) or 54th Avenue North (Exit 26).

hoodMarket: South Pinellas is the largest industrial market in the Tampa region, benefitting from the St. Pete-Clearwater International Airport and direct access to Interstate 275, which connects to Florida’s two primary arterial roadways, Interstates 4 and 75. South Pinellas is located within a same-day round-trip drive to all Florida markets. Industrial construction has been limited over the past decade, and as a result, the industrial inventory here is a bit older than the Tampa market average.,South Pinellas has benefitted from both traditional industrial demand as well as tenants’ more modern needs. Historically, the tenant mix in South Pinellas has been dominated by the aerospace and defense industries, but the rise of e-commerce has fueled industrial demand in warehouses targeting last-mile deliveries servicing the local population. Competition in this niche sector is becoming fierce, with the older inventory and relatively lower ceiling heights limiting the total available space for prospective tenants. The South Pinellas industrial market is now incredibly tight, with average occupancy rates near the highest on record.,Asking rents here vary widely across property types and due to South Pinellas’ large geography. However, industrial average rents are in general above the Tampa market average. Perhaps the market’s biggest draw for industrial tenants is the established inventory and industrial infrastructure, allowing most spaces to immediately fit a variety of needs.

hoodMarket: Southeast Broward is Broward County’s largest industrial area and sits on the county’s southern border with Miami-Dade County. This industrial locale spans from 215th Street/County Line Road to the south to Florida’s Ronald Regan Turnpike to the west, West Broward Boulevard the north, and the ocean to the west. Interstate 95 bisects this industrial area, while Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport is located in the center of Southeast Broward, and Port Everglade is in the northeastern corner of the area. Multiple nodes of industrial space exist in this area, but most properties are located on the Interstate 95 Corridor and around the airport.,Tenants are attracted to this industrial locale because of its proximity to significant trade infrastructure, including ports and the airports, in both the Miami and Fort Lauderdale areas, and connectivity to most of Florida’s primary highway arteries. Trade, logistics, and manufacturing companies are very active in this locale. The largest tenants in the area are BrandsMart, Alladin Carpet Mils, Vector Manufacturing, and Graybar.,Vacancies in Southeast Broward have been on the decline over the past decade, and they are below the Fort Lauderdale region average. Developers have been active in this area, adding some rentable industrial space, anddemand for industrial space has consistently outpaced supply in Southeast Broward since 2010. Rents are close to the Broward County average.

propOverview: Located in the heart of Broward County’s largest industrial area, 2301 SW 24th Avenue in Pembroke, Florida (Prologis Seneca Park 500) offers a sizable facility with high power options and cross-docking capabilities. Located just off the Pembroke Road exit on I-95, the 261,457 square-foot facility includes 7,431 square feet of office space, and the building can be divisible to half of the available space if necessary. Throughout the entire building, there are 60 dock-high doors, with 20 doors featuring pit levelers and 26 doors featuring edge of dock levelers, and three drive-ins, all of which are configured for cross-docking capabilities. The 1,200 amp, 480 volt electrical service offers the possibility for high powered machinery, and forklift charging areas are already in place. Additionally, the building features a 30’ clear height and 50’ x 50’ column spacing, as well as abundant parking options. There are six trailer parking stalls and 359 spots for employees. Prologis Seneca Park provides immediate access to I-95 and proximity to I-595, Florida’s Turnpike, I-75, and the Sawgrass Expressway, which lends well to distribution and logistics activities. The property also benefits from its convenient access to airports, rail lines, and freight ports. The Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport can be reached in 16 minutes, the Florida East Coast Rail Line can be reached in 18 minutes, and it is only 19 minutes to Port Everglades. The surrounding industrial area provides a strong local workforce, who can easily reach the building by car or by commuter rail, with the Hollywood Commuter Rail and the Sheridan Street Commuter Rail available in just nine and 12 minutes, respectively.

hoodMarket: One of Orlando’s largest industrial markets, Northwest Orange County stretches from Downtown Orlando to Lake Apopka to the west and runs north along Interstate 4 to Maitland Boulevard. Asking rents here vary across the relatively large geographical area, with properties closer to Interstate 4 renting at a premium. Overall, industrial rents are significantly lower than those in Seminole County directly to the east.,Industrial tenants benefit from accessibility to Central Florida as well as points west, north, and south. Interstate 4 runs as far west as Tampa and north to Daytona Beach, where it meets with the major north-south connector Interstate 95. Some of the largest industrial tenants in the area include Winn-Dixie, Sysco Corporation, and Coca Cola.,Another key thoroughfare is Orange Blossom Trail (U.S. 441), along which many of the area’s largest industrial properties are dotted. The road, which bisects the northwestern quadrant of Orange County, runs south through Kissimmee into Miami and north through Ocala and Gainesville to Georgia.

highlights: Turnkey kitchen solutions for delivery-only business models, dramatically cutting real estate and labor costs with 200 SF kitchens and flexible terms.,Spaces come equipped with walk-ins, floor drains, sinks, and hood systems, plus in-place permits that allow businesses to be up and running in weeks.,Located in the residential West End, one of Atlanta’s first streetcar suburbs and currently one of the most sought after neighborhoods to live in.,A 3-mile radius encompasses over 153,000 residents and last year combined for an annual consumer spending of over $300 million on food and alcohol.
propOverview:
Located in Atlanta’s residential West End neighborhood, 777 SW Oak Street is well-positioned for delivery-only business to thrive. The West End is one of Atlanta’s first streetcar suburbs, the location of historic homes and elegant architecture. It is now a cultural hub and one of the most sought after neighborhoods for young professionals and families. 777 SW Oak St is a revitalized industrial building within this historic district. The building offers turnkey kitchens complete with separate walk-in coolers, floor drains, sinks, and hood systems, and all that businesses need to bring is their specialized equipment. Kitchen spaces start at 200 square feet, and together with flexible terms, can help companies lower their real estate costs and spend more efficiently on labor. The focus is on providing space for delivery-only business models, catering to all sides of the restaurant industry: national chains, single locations, food entrepreneurs, and food truck owners. Delivery-only business models will benefit from the dense residential areas and the proximity to the schools of Georgia Tech, Georgia State University, Morehouse College, Spelman College, and Clark Atlanta University. There are 153,078 residents, 190,048 daytime employees, and 66,548 students in a 3-mile radius. Together this population combined to spend over $300 million in the last year on food and alcohol. The West End is known for being incredibly pedestrian- and bicycle-friendly and has access to the Atlanta BeltLine, which is 33 miles of multi-purpose trails. 777 SW Oak St is the premier opportunity to launch a new venture or grow an existing business in this vibrant community.
However, this offering provides much more than just real estate. Leasing this property grants restauranteurs access to a platform that will unlock their grandest visions. Our around the clock account managers will work with you to make sure every part of your operation is running smoothly, from integrating the location onto all the delivery platforms, to helping you tailor your menu to a delivery-only business model, to working with you to capture the growing trends and increase your revenue.

propOverview:
Apex Capital Realty is proud to present the opportunity to lease a freestanding building located in the Midtown neighborhood of Miami. The property features 1,800 SF of office space and over 4,000 SF of flex warehouse
space.
The Midtown Headquarter building features 17" ceilings, 6 street level roll-up garage doors, an oversize paved parking area and plenty of natural light.
This property is located next to the Midtown Miami development which is composed of of retail shops, apartments and an upcoming organic grocer. Currently there are over 2,600 residential units within a mile radius which houses over 7,000 residents.
The property also is blocks of the Wynwood Arts District which is a world recognized tourist destination that receives over 2,000,000 visitors per year. Wynwood is an evolving district that was originally composed of industrial warehouses that were converted into creative office and retail uses. After the rezoning of the district in 2015, Wynwood is now home to a flurry of development that include multiple mid-rise multifamily developments, hotels and office buildings. The property is also blocks away from The Miami Design District which is one of the largest outdoor luxury and design shopping districts.
The Property is easily accessible from Biscayne Blvd. N Miami Ave, I-95 and I-195. The site is also minutes away from Miami International Airport, Miami Beach and Downtown Miami. The site is also blocks away from the proposed Tri-Rail stations on 36 ST and 27th ST which could potential come online in 2020-21 and would connect all of the major tri-county urban areas.

propOverview:
DWNTWN Realty Advisors is pleased to present 816 NW 6th Avenue is available for lease. A flurry of investments has given way along the community’s main street in Fort Lauderdale, East Sunrise Boulevard. The success of downtown and Flagler Village, both booming with high-rise housing, pushed investors west across the railroad tracks, where land prices are lower. The neighborhood is said to be the new Wynwood of Fort Lauderdale.

propOverview:

There are multiple leasing options for this property with the smallest division containing approximately 4,008 SF in building 2.  Over 150" Feet of frontage along NW 26th Street. Location Description:
The subject property is located on the south side of NW 26th Street, between NW 3rd and 5th Avenues. To the East, The Wynwood Garage, home of WeWork and Punch Bowl Social, To the West, a new mix-used project by Sterling Bay is expected to deliver mid-2020. Additionally, the property is surrounded by a large number of ongoing developments including Wynwood Park, Wynwood Walk, The Moxy Hotel, The Wynwood Hotel, and more. Wynwood is an eclectic district in the urban core of Miami, Florida. It is home to art galleries, retail stores, antique shops, eclectic bars, artisanal eateries and one of the largest open-air street-art installations in the world. Today, Wynwood is recognized globally as a premier destination for art, fashion, innovation, and creative enterprise.

propOverview: 8020 NW 60th Street is located along a dense commercial corridor west of the Miami International Airport. Multiple suppliers, importers, and exporters have selected the area due to the proximity to major transportation routes, plus residential areas with shopping, dining and entertainment options. The Miami International Airport (MIA) is less than 10 miles to the building offering tenants easy access to the country’s largest international cargo airport. PortMiami is the largest passenger port in the world, and one of the largest cargo ports in the United States, and is a short 30-minute drive to the building. The Miami trade route not only serves South Florida's consumption needs but also primarily acts as a bridge between Miami, the Southeast, and the world, which has turned Miami into a significant global trade gateway. In 2014, ownership invested in a new roof, plumbing, electrical, and sprinkler systems for 8020 NW 60th Street. They also updated the office space to include new conference rooms and a renovated kitchen area. Tenants will benefit from the proximity to downtown Miami, major shopping destinations, and the area's many golfing amenities.

propOverview: The warehouse and office space at 6335 Downing Street offers an excellent opportunity to lease a centrally located space with convenient access to I-25, I-70, and Highway 36 which are less than a 15-minute drive from the property.  The building rests on a fenced and gated 1.42-acre lot and features 3,500 square feet of office space with one main and three private offices.  In addition, the warehouse space sports a 17’ clear height with four 12' x 14' drive-in doors, and 650 amps of 480-volt, 3-phase power.  Employers can rest easy knowing that manufacturing jobs make up 20% of the labor market in the immediate area meaning a skilled labor force will consistently be available. The facility's position within unincorporated Adams County includes a 3.6% tax rate which is lower than most surrounding areas.  The property is located in the North Washington industrial district that is home to many prominent companies such as Anheuser-Busch and Boise Cascade Wood Products.  The building is only a five-minute drive to the Denver Merchandise Mart which hosts trade shows, consumer shows, conferences, and special events. Employees will also enjoy the brief, five-minute drive to various quick-eat restaurants in the vicinity.

propOverview:
This warehouse and distribution center is brand new to the market. It’s a high bay warehouse space which has been the Pepsi Cola distribution site for over 25 years! The demised space available is 11,200 s.f. of column free warehouse 22' high ceilings including 2,000sf office space. This industrial building is ideal for warehousing, distribution, light manufacturing, and many other industrial uses allowed by Brookfield’s IRC zoning regulations.
 The site is designed to accommodate tractor trailer parking and handling for delivery or distribution. The available space is column free designed with a loading dock with leveler and ability to easily add an additional dock. The space contains a large drive-in door to provide access to the warehouse. The space includes 2,400 s.f. of well-maintained office space with a reception area, conference room, kitchen/break rooms, serviced by office and warehouse bathrooms. See the attached floor plans.
 Parking is provided for 32 passenger vehicles in front of the building and plenty of room available for overnight parking of trucks and trailers in the dock area at the rear of the building. The truck area is secured with fencing and large steel gates. 
 This facility is located near Route 7/Federal Rd in Brookfield and is a short distance from several Super 7 and I-84 exits. It has immediate and easy congestion free access to & from the I-84, I-684,and Rte. Super 7 Northeast transportation hub and provides convenient movement and mobility throughout the region and the Northeast. This close proximity to I-84 of the location is the Gateway for access into Eastbound New England and Westbound New York, New Jersey and PA. Metropolitan NY and NJ is only one hour South.
 The space is available for lease at $6.95/sf NNN. Contact the broker George Walker at 203-733-0692 to discuss your industrial real estate needs and tour the building today!

propOverview:
Office and Retail Space in East Rock!
East Rock Center is a mixed-use redevelopment of a 200,000- square foot historic industrial complex. The property has been modernized and upgraded to accommodate the needs of today's businesses.
 
Narang Property Group worked with Javier Ferro to design and restore the former factory building. Built in 1908 and redeveloped in 2016, East Rock Center offers many options for build-to-suit office space from 5,000 to 40,000 square feet. 
*Please note there are currently no office spaces available for immediate occupancy. All spaces listed for lease are designed and built for each tenants. 
 
The current tenant roster includes:
 
- mActivity - An innovative fitness center 
- East Rock Brewing Company - New Haven's largest craft brewery & beer garden
- Rebel Salon - An experiential salon
- Cornell Scott Hill Health Corporation - Corporate Office 
- Outfront Media - Corporate Office & Production Facility
- Ingenius Prep - Corporate Office
- World Champion Taekwondo
Other amenities include: 
- Garage parking with 100 spaces (Discounted monthly parking for tenants)
- Free surface parking lot with 45 spaces
- Discounted corporate rates for on-site fitness center
- Craft brewery and beer garden on-site
- Beautiful lobby with living green wall, elevator access, video intercom
- Secured access control to all spaces including tenant office using mobile phone as digital key
- High-speed fiber connectivity
- State-of-the art security and building systems  
Ideally located just minutes from downtown New Haven, Yale University, East Rock Park and Interstates I-91 & I-95, East Rock Center offers convenience and easy access.
Visit www.eastrockcenter.com or click on 'Building Website' below for more information.
